Deputy President William Ruto has said amending the constitution should not be informed by the interest of those in power. In a thinly veiled attack on the proponents of BBI, the DP claimed the push to change the constitution is because those in power are not happy with certain provisions that don&rsquo;t align their political interests he was speaking at his Karen residence here in Nairobi during a fellowship with various groups of religious leaders from Kiambu county.